Company Overview of Wilmington Trust Investment Advisors, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
MTB Investment Advisors, Inc. is a privately owned investment manager. The firm also provides advisory services to its clients. It primarily provides its services to charitable organizations and corporations. The firm also manages accounts for high net worth individuals, banking or thrift institutions, pension and profit sharing plans, investment companies, not-for-profit organizations, endowments, foundations, utility decommissioning trust fund, state or municipal government entities, and unions. It manages separate client-focused equity, fixed income, and balanced portfolios. The firm also launches and manages equity, fixed income, and balanced mutual funds for its clients. It invests in t...
MTB Investment Advisors, Inc. is a privately owned investment manager. The firm also provides advisory services to its clients. It primarily provides its services to charitable organizations and corporations. The firm also manages accounts for high net worth individuals, banking or thrift institutions, pension and profit sharing plans, investment companies, not-for-profit organizations, endowments, foundations, utility decommissioning trust fund, state or municipal government entities, and unions. It manages separate client-focused equity, fixed income, and balanced portfolios. The firm also launches and manages equity, fixed income, and balanced mutual funds for its clients. It invests in the public equity and fixed income markets of the United States. The firm invests in growth stocks of small-cap, mid-cap, and large-cap companies to make its equity investments. For its fixed income investments, it invests in corporate debt securities, commercial paper, certificates of deposit, United States government securities, intermediate-term and long-term fixed income securities, and municipal securities. The firm employs a combination of fundamental, thematic, technical, and quantitative analysis while making its investments. It also uses a combination of a top-down and a bottom-up stock picking approach to create its portfolios. The firm benchmarks the performance of its equity portfolios against the S&P/BARRA Growth Index, S&P 500 Index, S&P/BARRA Mid Cap 400 Growth Index, and Russell 2000 Growth Index. It benchmarks the performance of its fixed income portfolios against the Barclays Capital Intermediate Government/Credit Index and Barclays Capital Aggregate Index. The firm benchmarks the performance of its enhanced cash portfolios against the iMoney Net First Tier Institutional Index, Merrill Lynch 1 Year Treasury Index, and Merrill Lynch 1-3 year Governments/Corp Index. It conducts in-house research to make its investments. The firm was founded in June 1995 and is based in Baltimore, Maryland with additional offices in Washington, District of Columbia; Harrisburg, Pennsylvania; New York, New York; Hanover, Pennsylvania; Buffalo, New York; Rochester, New York; State College, Pennsylvania; and Horsham, Pennsylvania. MTB Investment Advisors, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of M&T Bank., Inc.
